		"description": "<p><em><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-15739a6b-7fff-df7e-de97-bc0df31f75ba\"><strong>Type:</strong> Substance; <strong>Level:</strong> 17; <strong>Element:</strong> Air or Water</span></em></p>\n<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-6ca396b9-7fff-51fe-65c7-5bd86b53fb8f\">By spending 7 spell points, your blast sucks the air from the target&rsquo;s lungs or fills them with water. Creatures hit must succeed a Constitution saving throw or take 1d6 ongoing damage and begin holding their breath; they can repeat this saving throw at the end of each of their turns to regain their breath and end the effect. Non-breathing creatures are immune to this effect. This otherwise follows the rules for drowning and suffocation.</span></p>",
